Leading car dealer CMC Motors Group recently launched three new Mazda car models into the market. The exclusive franchise holder for the Mazda brand in Kenya, while expanding its presence, unveiled two SUVs, CX-9 and CX-5, and a truck, BT-50. They were launched during a cocktail ceremony at Radisson Blu Hotel on August 8. Speaking during the launch, CMC brand manager Robert Gichuki said the three Mazda models were designed to ensure the consumer gets their monies' worth. He said the new entrants in the market cut across the board to combine luxury and comfort to meet the needs of todayâ€™s modern dynamic families.